  "description": "\nThe **radio button** (also known as an option button) is a form element used when users need to make\na choice between two or more mutually exclusive, related options. With radio buttons, users can choose\nonly one option.\n",
  "name": "Radio Button",
  "usage": "\nIt is recommended to have your `<input type=\"radio\">` be inside `<label>` and the `for` attribute\nof the label must match the `id` attribute of the input. When grouping inputs, use the `role=\"group\"`\nattribute combine with aria-labelledby`.\n\n```html\n<!--Single input-->\n<label for=\"unique_id\" class=\"radio u-mb--\">\n   <input id=\"unique_id\" type=\"radio\" class=\"radio__input\" name=\"radio_group\"/>\n   <span class=\"radio__label\">Option Label</span>\n</label>\n\n<!--Multiple inputs-->\n<div role=\"group\" aria-labelledby=\"group-label\" class=\"form__fieldset\">\n  <div id=\"group-label\" class=\"form__label\">\n   Select Option(s)\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <div>\n      <label for=\"unique_id\" class=\"radio u-mb--\">\n        <input id=\"unique_id\" type=\"radio\" class=\"radio__input\" name=\"radio_group\"/>\n        <span class=\"radio__label\">Option Label</span>\n      </label>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n      <label for=\"unique_id1\" class=\"radio u-mb--\">\n        <input id=\"unique_id1\" type=\"radio\" class=\"radio__input\" name=\"radio_group\"/>\n        <span class=\"radio__label\">Option Label</span>\n      </label>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nAnimations: The radio button animates on click, and uses a standard easing when it is checked and unchecked. Duration: The duration of the animation is 100ms in either direction.  \n",
  "version": "1.1.3",
  "browsers": "chrome, safari, firefox, ie11, edge\n"
